INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('36','body','Textile','As Bitch Kitty Racing has just finished it\'s first full quarter since we went online, it was time that we looked over our revenues. As John has earlier \"reported\":http://bitchkittyracing.com/news/bitch-kitty-revenue-report, the figures exceeded our best expectations and we easily met our goal of being able to purchase a six pack of beer in Mexico. \r\n\r\nI was curious as how we achieved such incredible success and decided to investigate just which fascinating ads were appearing on the web site. First let me backtrack a bit. _Getting_ these ads in the first place proved a bit more complicated than expected. To begin with, we swear. Not gratuitously, of course, but rather only when it is absolutely needed to effectively communicate artistic intent. Naturally, this had to go. Google does not approve of swearing, even artistically. \r\n\r\nAll offending words removed, we tried again. All that was left, as John put it, were \r\n\r\nbq. \"two canine terms, two mild oaths, one prostitute, one religious reference, and a donkey. Not so bad.\" \r\n\r\nBut it was. Still no love from Google. What is an aspiring online magazine such as *Bitch Kitty Racing* without Google ads? \r\n\r\nBut then it occurred to us:\r\n\r\nbq. \"Bitch.\" \r\n\r\nHmm. We were (and are) rather attached to the name, as John has earlier explained. In fact, we had actually changed the name at one point, only to realize that Bitch Kitty Racing was the One True Domain for us. Drastic action needed to be taken.\r\n\r\nJohn wrote an email. Surprisingly, Google was very cool about it. A quick response and we were in. \r\n\r\nEventually, the ads began and I noticed a few oddities. These oddities increased and finally yesterday I noticed these ads,  above one another.\r\n\r\n!<r:content part=\"bombs\" />!\r\n\r\nAfter noticing ads where I could either buy or sell a kidney (unfortunately did not make a screenshot of this and I realize that none of you believe me), I decided to look further into this. And this time, I made screenshots. \r\n\r\n!<r:content part=\"transplants\" />!\r\n\r\nApparently, Bitch Kitty Racing readers are a lot of old and infertile, bomb-sniffing, terminally ill gourmets who like to dine in Ireland. \r\n\r\n_Really._\r\n\r\nGoogle is justly famous for its brilliant mathematical algorithms that allow me to find that one little bit of info I need with little more than a simple query. I recently read that help wanted ads for Google (at least one famous billboard) are encrypted. You have to be smart enough to decrypt the billboard to even know that it\'s either an ad or for Google. When searching these days I can avoid mucking about with Boolean logic and such and simply write \"how to upload images in Ruby on Rails.\" I usually get what I want. Absolutely brilliant. \r\n\r\nWhere are these algorithms and the brilliant employees who wrote them now? Just how do \"Original American SWAT Boots\" relate to going to the wrong bathroom in a chic Northwest restaurant? How do pet tear stain removers relate to filling one\'s bathtub with jello? What _are_ pet tear stain removers? And most of all, how am I going to get rich and retire on the lovely Spanish island of Mallorca with such ads? \r\n\r\nThe answer is easy: money. People buy keywords without regard to the context. If a given combination of keywords shows up in the text, then that ad has to appear. And John has a, well, colorful choice of words. Stripped of his artistic ability to swear, he was forced to increase his vocabulary (already huge, thanks to those years in Art School) and the results can be seen below.\r\n\r\nI have provided here a small gallery for you with some of our choicest ads. I will let you make the connections to any articles presented here at Bitch Kitty Racing.\r\n\r\n\r\n<script src=\"http://www.google-analytics.com/urchin.js\" type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n</script>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n_uacct = \"UA-1192760-1\";\r\nurchinTracker();\r\n</script>','21');
INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('37','body','Textile','Hate to bring it up, folks, but it\'s true.  Please shop at the Bitch Kitty Store.  Buying from us eliminates your need to feel guilty for supporting evil, kitten-killing corporations and shifts the guilt on to us for selling out.\r\n\r\nOh, God, I love Christmas.  I look forward to it for months.  Every year I get back at my parents for not taking me to Disneyland when I was six by telling them I\'m gay on Christmas morning.  Oh, the tears and wailing!  Oh, the wondering where they failed!  They\'re both so senile they have problems remembering where I fall in line in the child roster, or when my birthday is, or what precisely my name might be.  This year I\'ll probably be able to ruin both Christmas morning AND dinner!  \r\n\r\nThe actual truth of the matter is highly unimportant compared to the entertainment value of this prank.\r\n\r\nMy other favorite \"trick the old folks\" game begins when one of them starts complaining and asking to leave.  We go out to the car and I turn it on, let it idle for a few moments, then turn it off.  \"We\'re here, Dad,\" I\'ll say.  \r\n\r\n\"Oh,\" he\'ll say, looking confused.  \"Okay.\"\r\n\r\nThen back in we go for more turkey loaf.\r\n<p>\r\n</p>  \r\n\r\nSupport us.  You know you want to.  Shop at the Bitch Kitty Store.\r\n\r\n\"The BITCH KITTY STORE\":http://astore.amazon.com/bitchkittyrac-20','22');
