INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('73','body','Textile','A musty cardboard box sat in the middle of the bedroom floor in my new apartment, the words \"AMY\'S UNDERWEAR\" scrawled across opposite sides.  Masking tape haphazardly held down the flaps in a failing effort to keep the contents inside.  This was my soon-to-be ex-husband\'s handiwork, his reaction to my leaving after almost 20 years.  Pack me up.  Tape me up.  Send me away.  Trust me  the idea of the new life ahead was liberating and I wanted to unpack.\r\n\r\n!/img/112.jpg!\r\n\r\nAwaiting the arrival of the box\'s contents was a new dresser complete with green velvet-lined drawers.  These were drawers you would expect to find in an upscale lingerie store, offering decadent treasures of all colors, shapes, sizes and textures, waiting to be filled.\r\n\r\nI ripped off the masking tape.  The flaps popped up like some jack-in-the-box toy.  All that was missing was the clown jumping out of the box, but then again my ex-husband sealed it closed from the outside.   I began pulling underwear from the box.  One-by-one the assortment of bras and panties amassed upon the floor.  To my horror, my eyes met with a sea of beige nylon that blended in with the apartment carpeting.  \r\n\r\nWhat the hell happened?  I used to have luscious lingerie that made me feel like I was ready at a moment\'s notice to act upon a sexual impulse.  I owned lingerie that was absolute tease to anyone who might even  peek at it.  Where did the black teddy go?  Where are the garters?  When did I become nothing but beige?\r\n\r\nI held up one panty, another beige brief  with a high waist and low-cut legs.  So practical.  It reminded me of my maternity underwear, the ones my ex-husband ridiculed:, \"Hey, I could park my truck in these.\"  There were quite a few of those briefs, reminders of how uncomfortable I was with how I looked, pregnant or not.  I pulled out another pair of panties; this time the elastic on the legs was actually falling off, the fabric so threadbare it looked lacy.  I recalled how so often I would hold onto things past their prime, because I might still be able to get some use out of them.   If struck by a car, I would have been so embarrassed by those panties. \r\n\r\nI pleaded with the box, \"Please tell me my bras exude more intrigue than my beige panties.\"  No such luck.  The bras were just as beige as the panties.  The theme of worn elastic was continued with one bra in particular,  its straps shortened up to compensate for elastic stretching out over the years.  I knew that bra well.  The straps repeatedly dropped off my shoulders, and not because of some moment of lustful teasing.  A woman versus strap struggle ensued usually at work in a moment of trying to look professional.  Digging through the pile, I pulled out one bra that lost its purpose long ago: a nursing bra.  I have no idea what it was doing in there, it just was there and it was beige.  The bra did provide a certain yardstick  it was around seventeen years old.  I found another, a flimsy support number with little or no support except for the underwire.  The nylon held the general form of each breast, stretched out over time.  My bustline could not help but migrate south.\r\n\r\nI wanted to find the bras and panties worthy of my new dresser and its elegant drawers.  There should have been all sorts of colors and textures and shapes, like my capricious nature.  But all I found was undifferentiated beige.  Worse yet, under the day\'s outfit was more beige.  \r\n\r\nBeige  that was for the woman who acted as a single parent for the majority of her marriage.  Beige  that was for the woman whose husband told her, \"If you were one of my employees, I would have fired you by now.\"  Beige  that was for the woman who went to bed each night dreading the required intimacy.  Beige  it\'s not a color, it\'s an attitude. \r\n\r\nI hated looking at all that beige.  I hated being beige, invisible, undesirable, and complacent.  Maybe it took seventeen years to wind up this way, but I now I could change it faster than I unpacked it if I wanted.  Now was the opportunity to really set out on my new adventure as a single woman.  Forget blending in; I wanted people to know I\'m here and offering something.  I wanted people to know about all the wonderful colors and textures that make up Amy.  It doesn\'t have to be boastful, either, just not beige.\r\n\r\nYes, I bought all that beige underwear but now I was going to let it blend in somewhere else  back in the jack-in-the-box carton.  I really wanted to put the clown back in it, too.  The only thing left now was to get the rest of the beige off of me.  I wanted to feel the teddy and the garters from years ago.  I wanted to feel my emerging self in a teddy and garters now. \r\n\r\nI left the new drawers empty and made my way to the lingerie department in the local mall, on an expedition for something new and exciting.  To my surprise, there were plenty of bras and panties that did not come in beige, but rather real colors such as red, black, blue, purple, and green.  So many lovely, frilly, adventurous bras and panties everywhere!  I must have spent an hour just looking at all the different options, all those different adventures.  Eventually, I picked something off the rack  an all-lace bra in black with red satin ribbon trim that laced in front.  As I admired the piece, the bra fitter passed by and then stopped alongside me.  She looked at the bra, then at my bustline, and then at the bra again.  \r\n\r\n\"You\'ve got the wrong size\" she announced.  \r\n\r\n\"But it\'s the same size I\'ve had for years,\" I replied.  \r\n\r\n\"Then you\'ve had the wrong fit all those years.\"  \r\n\r\nShe could not summed up the last seventeen years any better.  \r\n\r\nWe went to a dressing room, where I stripped down to my beige bra.  Oh god, one of my worst fears realized:  exposing my beige bra in a lingerie department.  Over an hour and many combinations later, I emerged a in my new, true shape as a woman.  I had some pale yellow combinations that are silky with full lace cups on the bra and a lace insert in the panties.  There is the bright red lace combination, quite translucent, that made me look  like I\'m driving the Indy 500 on Valentine\'s Day.  There is the black silk combination with lace inserts that look like autumn leaves have softly touched down here and there.  Despite a fuller figure than I knew I had, no longer was I slouched over in a poorly fitting undergarment.  I looked at the new woman in the mirror, shoulders back, chin up, sensual bustline where it was supposed to be, not halfway to the South Pole.   As I stood looking at myself in yet another saucy combination, I told the bra fitter I wished to wear this out and to throw away the last of my beige underwear.  \r\n\r\nI liked the woman the mirror.  I liked her attitude.  Even dressed, all those wonderful colors and textures were still there to be seen.   This woman wouldn\'t apologize just to keep the peace.  She wouldn\'t explain herself.  She had no regrets.  She had no fear of the future.  \r\n\r\nThe black bra held me up as I paid for my purchases, then something caught my eye.  \"Excuse me,\" I said to the salesgirl in the beige skirt, \"Would you help me with those leather pants?\"  \r\n\r\n\r\n<script src=\"http://www.google-analytics.com/urchin.js\" type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n</script>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n_uacct = \"UA-1192760-1\";\r\nurchinTracker();\r\n</script>','39');
