INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('514','body','Textile','Im a good little American, \"responsible, reliable, dependable, and lots of other things that end in ibble,\":http://www.reddwarf.co.uk and I have completed my tax return for 2006.  Yes, I know its already January 6.  I wouldnt have waited this long but my day job (I work as principal of \"Sweet Valley High\":http://www.randomhouse.com/sweetvalley/) just gave me my W2.  Theyre not good Americans.  I think theyre actually \"Communists.\":http://bitchkittyracing.com/news/everything-old-is-new-again  At the very least theyre bastards.\r\n\r\nBut I digress.\r\n\r\nI can and do deduct expenses related to Bitch Kitty Racing.  This is a legitimate business  I am a legitimate business owner.  But nowhere does my accountant have a form that allows me to deduct dating expenses.\r\n\r\nWhat the dilly, yo?\r\n\r\nHow do you think I _come up_ with all this stuff?  This isnt fiction.  This is real!  I throw myself on the altar of dating madness every single day for the reading enjoyment of the Bitch Kitty Army.  Wheres my tax credit?\r\n\r\nAs I go through my receipts (I keep them all filed in a mound on my desk) I find jewelry expenses, hotel expenses, dinner expenses, psychotherapy expenses, adult store expenses, not to mention sheets, a new bed, decent furniture, a good \"make out couch,\":http://bitchkittyracing.com/articles/nesting and fitted clothing.  \r\n\r\nAnd what about the carryover credits? Can I deduct all the getting my ass to this state in the first place expenses?  There is twenty-two years of dating experience housed in this body.  Other businesses have deductions for investment expenses.  This is all straight research.  They cant fine me just because I happen to enjoy it.  And what about business losses?  How much can I charge for being cheated on?  Or having my ex call me over Christmas to tell me she got married? \r\n\r\nIm using insurance tables to calculate damage expense right now.  Lets see, $50,000 for an arm, $100,000 for an eye . . .  hmmm . . . Aha!  There it is black and white: heart failure, one million dollars.\r\n\r\nThe IRS is going to _love_ this.\r\n\r\n\"Bitch Kitty Travel\":http://bitchkittyracing.com/about/?c=Bitch-Kitty-Travel\r\n','144');
