INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('548','body','Textile','So youve recently broken up with your lover.  We here at Bitch Kitty Racing express our deepest sympathy for you. We know how much it hurts.  To help you through this troubled and _temporary_ time, we have compiled a few real-world tips.  Theyre not painless, and theyre probably not on any Psychological Health Top Ten lists, but this is the real world.  Who the hell wants to get in touch with your inner child at a time like this?!\r\n\r\n_Psychologists schmycologists!_\r\n\r\nThese are in no particular order, so read them all.     \r\n\r\n* Eat.  Go to the corner deli and buy yourself some damned sandwiches.  Eat at least one a day, and it would be nice if you ate two.\r\n* Put on that horrendously ridiculous Blue Tooth headset that you bought but have been too embarrassed to wear in public because it makes you look like an idiot.  Call all your sympathetic friends and kvetch.  If anyone says: I told you so, hang up and never speak to that person again.  If anyone offers helpful advice hang up, but you may speak to them at some point in the future.  \r\n* Get a big box and place everything of your lovers in it, and also any memorabilia.  You do not need to be remembering that one weekend you spent together, mooning over pictures, or listening to the song you first danced to together.  Take that box and triple tape it shut, but dont throw it away!  Some items in it might be valuables youll want later, and your lovers things can be used as a bargaining tool to get back yours.  Do take that box, though, and lock it in a dark corner in the basement or garage. Do not open it.  And in this digital age, make sure you clean your hard drive and burn all pictures and letters onto a DVD, but dont look at any!  Throw the DVD in the box.\r\n* Start cleaning.  Scour your home.  Get rid of any evidence at all that your lover existed, from anything you missed in you Lovers Stuff sweep to stray hairs and skin flakes.  Dont forget the bathroom cabinet because there are two toothbrushes in there.\r\n* Eat again.\r\n* Clean your bedroom thoroughly and make sure your bedding is fresh.  Make sure you have an adequate supply of condoms and lube in the nightstand  youve probably been drinking and talking to your friends: if they love you theyll get you out of the house later and you have no judgment right now.  Yes, you will hate yourself in the morning.\r\n* Do not allow your lover into your house. Do not go to your lovers house.  These are the physical spaces where you explored your intimacy and all the feelings will flood back. \r\n* DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.  DO NOT engage in break-up sex.\r\n\r\n_Break-up sex drags out the pain and suffering of loss and is completely avoidable self-flagellation. It does more harm than good.  If you think you might engage in break-up sex, drag a cheese grater over your genitalia and imagine its your heart.  You can live without sex, but you cannot live without a heart._\r\n\r\n*Eat again.\r\n\r\n* Exercising is great, even though its probably next to impossible right now.  You need to improve your self-confidence and sense of accomplishment.  Though its hard and seems pointless when your world has just ended and even the stars weep for you, you need a daily victory.  You also need to feel hot right now.  \r\n* Avoid like a rat-infested thirteenth century Paris any weepy music.  It might seem stupid to cry uncontrollably for days while listening to Im Walking on Sunshine by Katrina and the Waves, but wallowing in your pain is stupider.  It also makes it easier to clean and exercise.\r\n* No matter what your lover did _to_ you or did not do _for_ you, forgive all transgressions.  The relationship is over.  Clean out your heart like you cleaned out your homeyour heart _is_ your home.\r\n* If you are a previous smoker, make sure you have lots of nicotine gum around.  The last thing you need to do is start smoking again.  I suppose this goes for drug addicts as well.  By smoking, as well as some other drugs, your body is trying to raise its serotonin levels so you do not suffer from depression or sleep deprivation.  Go for walks, go to a tanning bed, exercise, create, clean, but do not revert to your previous addiction. Easier said than done, but now you know why you want to revert and hopefully you can avoid it.\r\n* Make a to-do list every morning, and keep it reasonable with simple tasks like cleaning the cat box or doing the dishes.  Make sure it is completed every night before you go to bed.  Write the Great American Novel is not a suitable entry on this to-do list.  Youll feel better if you accomplish a task every single day.\r\n\r\nWhile by no means a cure-all, Bitch Kitty Racing hopes these tips help you through this difficult time.  We feel for you.  Hang in there!  The sense of grief and loss is temporary. You will feel better in time.\r\n\r\nAnd also remember, dear God and oh no, youre going to fall in love again!  \r\n\r\n\"_Get the Soundtrack to How to Break Up here_\":http://bitchkittyracing.com/bitch-kitty-records/imixes/how-to-break-up/\r\n','155');
