INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('570','body','Textile','We here at Bitch Kitty Racing are very excited that you will be president in just two short years.  We seriously have been looking forward to it since the day you took office.  Please go to charm school so you don\'t royally bugger it all up within the first two weeks.  Personally, we think it\'s cute that you\'re so abrasive.  Also, if you could tell Senator Obama to pull his head out of his _clouds_ and consent to be your running mate now we\'d be eternally grateful.  Clinton/Obama in \'08?  C\'mon!  You\'ve already won!  It wouldn\'t even matter what you did when you took office; it\'d be like America just had its first child.  No matter how much the two of you threw up, the entire world would just stand around shaking its head slowly and gushing, \"Oh my God, isn\'t it _ADORABLE?!\"_  We can only hope that you will not prove to be like Fendi\'s current line.\r\n\r\nNo, Fendi has nothing to do with either politics or this discussion, but the new line is so fucking \"awful\":http://www.eluxury.com/browse/product_detail.jhtml?styleid=11248968&SectionID=5000 that it serves as a useful simile.  The new line makes all wearers look short, fat, and pregnant, and not in a good way. What happened?  Did Fendi move from Italy to Iowa?\r\n\r\nMoving on back to the politics of which Bitch Kitty Racing should never speak: Senator Obama, STOP!  Be Senator Clinton\'s running mate.  You do not have the experience to be president now, but after eight years of vice presidency you will.  The democrats will a viable and reasonable candidate for 2016, unlike the 2000 fiasco of the Inventor of the Internet, Al Gore.  Apparently he also invented global warming.  What\'s next, Al?  The tree?  Did you invent that, too?  And Crazy Al, by the way, is married to Tipper Gore, the conservative Christian white woman Southerner behind the \"Parents\' Music Resource Center.\":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parents_Music_Resource_Center  Thank God for Tipper and Wal-Mart, or we\'d have no morals at all!\r\n\r\nLast thought: the fact that all politicians are slimeballs is a result of the electoral process.  In order to get elected, they have to please a majority of the population, most of whom think all politicians are slimeballs and don\'t vote.  Until all state and federal congresses reform or end special interest lobbies, and until all state and federal congresses enact a one item per bill rule, politicians ARE slimeballs and have no choice to be otherwise.  They\'re criminals, actually: thieves and liars.  It\'s like a personality test.  \"Do you want a political office?  You do?  Please step away from my children/liquor cabinet/wallet.\"\r\n\r\nNice war, by the way!  Really enjoying it, thank you!  Great death toll!  Wonderful financing!  \r\n\r\nWait.  Where were we?  And this, dear reader, this is why Bitch Kitty Racing does not discuss politics.  Even pleasant events evoke images of\r\n\r\nWHOA!\r\n\r\nI\'m not making this up: a bald eagle just killed a dog in the alley!  Holy crap!  POW!!!  Death from above!  Have you seen an eagle?  They\'re HUGE up here, literally three feet tall with a wingspan the length of a VW Beetle.  Oh my god, that poor dog!  The eagle\'s just standing on it, clawing its neck.  Oh, there he goes!  He\'s flying off with it!  HA!\r\n\r\nWow, WAY too much symbolism here.','163');
