INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('577','body','Markdown','One of the great things about living in the richest country in the world is consumer choice.  No matter what the good or service, we can always go next door and find the same good or service.  This creates a wonderfully competitive environment in which the customer has myriad choices for anything.  Don\'t like the way your car dealership is treating you?  Go next door.  Most cars are fabulous these days, and all will serve your needs.  Don\'t like the way your cell phone company totally ignored your needs after you\'ve been a loyal customer for eight years?  Go next door, I\'m sure they have similar phones and similar plans.\r\n\r\nThe backfire is that there seems to be something called \"industry standard\" out there, as in: \"Our customer service is industry standard.\"  So, Bitch Kitty Racing would like to ask those firms what is their competitive edge?  Why should anyone choose your product when you just admitted it is neither better nor worse than your competitor\'s?  Industry standard is a stupid sales pitch.  It\'s ridiculous to think that anyone would foster a business relationship with your firm when you have just promised to be the same as everyone else.  And to survive, you need relationships, not customers.\r\n\r\nIdiots.\r\n\r\nBitch Kitty Racing is here for you, the individual.  That is our competitive edge.  You may have noticed we\'ve begun answering questions.  We do that because they have interesting answers.  They are also a direct link to our readers, who accquire names and personalities.  There is another reason we answer questions: because you asked.\r\n\r\nThere is an old joke which is appropriate here:\r\n\r\nQ: What is the difference between God and a bartender?\r\n\r\nA: God doesn\'t think he\'s a bartender.\r\n\r\nAs fully half of our staff is a bartender, it is his right to know everything there is to know in the world, or at least have an opinion on it.  Do you have a question?  Ask!  Want to know how to make the perfect Martini?  Have a concern about dating strategy?  Want to know why a hydrogen fuel cell works?  Wondering why your frites aren\'t as good as ours?  Need help picking out a good Cotes d\'Provence?  Need a good honest mechanic in Seattle or Bellingham?\r\n\r\nAsk: <john@bitchkittyracing.com>\r\n\r\nBitch Kitty Racing is the property of two real people: Keith and John.  Our names are on this site and we will never whore it out pitching things we do not actually use.  We will not sell ring tones, offer free iPods for answering stupid questions, or ANY product or service we have not tried.  Period.  If you see it here, it has a seal of approval from us.\r\n\r\nGet THAT from anyone else!\r\n\r\nAgain, any questions, comments, suggestions, or complaints, about anything at all, email: <john@bitchkittyracing.com>\r\n\r\nHere\'s the answer to question I received about [mezcal.](http://bitchkittyracing.com/articles/mezcal-ay-caramba/)\r\n\r\nAddendum\r\nFebruary 4, 2005\r\n\r\nBitch Kitty TV is hosted by Revver.  We do not have control of their advertising, so I guess we just sold out for TV.  So, I\'ll have to say \"all the stores offered by us are endorsed by us.\"  \r\n\r\nBut on the bright side, we now have a TV show!','165');
