INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('580','body','Markdown','I have received mail concerning the fix for the mushroomed strut tower crown.  This is the resource with which I started: [North American Motoring](http://www.northamericanmotoring.com/forums/showthread.php?t=86796)\r\n\r\nIf your dealer will not address the problem I suggest hooking up with an independent mechanic or speed shop in your area.  Your mechanic can set up any new equipment to feel just like stock, if you so desire.  Talk with him or her about your daily needs; that\'s the best place to set your car.  Be aware that with new suspension equipment you\'ve probably just blown your street stock classification for Solo competition.  That sucks, and I\'m sorry.  It was so nice to smoke the competition right out of the box with our superior automobiles, but now we have to find out how the other half lives.\r\n\r\nI am reluctant to recommend any one system.  Your personal needs will dictate your fix.  I am looking at Dinan upgrades, but they\'re expensive.  I also do no use my Mini as a daily driver, but only as a luxury go-kart.  In Seattle, I will never tighten it down all the way.  There are far too many potholes here and I have no doubt I\'d hate the ride.  To be perfectly honest, the only time I\'ve really ever appreciated the ride at all was on track days.  On real roads, I cringe at every jounce, not for my kidneys, but because the car really seems to hate it.  Apparently, it does.\r\n\r\nStill, they\'re awesome cars.  Let\'s hope Mini and BMW own up to this. If you or anyone you know is starting a class action lawsuit let me know, I\'ll post the info here.\r\n\r\nLet\'s irritatedly motor!\r\n\r\n<john@bitchkittyracing.com>\r\n\r\nP.S.  Have they stopped that damned ridiculous advertising campaign?  It made me embarrassed to own a Mini! Jeez, it was almost as bad as the current VW GTI/Rabbit campaign, which is also embarrassing but makes me giggle in delight because a Mini is faster.  Oh yeah, I said it!  Bring it on, GTI owners!\r\n\r\nWe\'re faster, we\'re faster, nyah nyah nyah nyah nyah nyah!\r\n\r\nThough I do utterly respect the bare bones Rabbit.  Cheaper than a Mini, and goes like hell.  Too bad it\'s so slow.\r\n\r\nNyah nyah nyah nyah nyah nyah!','166');
