INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('653','excerpt','Markdown','I have received mail concerning the fix for the mushroomed strut tower crown.  This is the resource with which I started: [North American Motoring](http://www.northamericanmotoring.com/forums/showthread.php?t=86796)\r\n\r\nIf your dealer will not address the problem I suggest hooking up with an independent mechanic or speed shop in your area.  Your mechanic can set up any new equipment to feel just like stock, if you so desire.  Talk with him or her about your daily needs; that\'s the best place to set your car.  Be aware that with new suspension equipment you\'ve probably just blown your street stock classification for Solo competition.  That sucks, and I\'m sorry.  It was so nice to smoke the competition right out of the box with our superior automobiles, but now we have to find out how the other half lives.\r\n','166');
INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('655','body','Textile','Hot diggity dog!\r\n\r\nBitch Kitty Racing, its parents and siblings are moving this weekend!  Hooray!  We no longer have to live in a barn in France where ze mice eat ze wires and we get that (fucking) 500 error once a week.\r\n\r\nOur Teutonic overlords are upgrading our little <a href=\"http://www.uhaul.com/supergraphics/images/graphics/classic_nevada2.jpg\">racing airplane</a> of a host to something a little more robust.  Think <a href=\"http://www.aerospaceweb.org/aircraft/transport-m/c5/\">C-5 Heavy Transport.</a>\r\n\r\nYou may have noticed Bitch Kitty Racing is kind of big.  When you start wandering around, there\'s actually quite a bit of stuff to look at and play with.  Our new Content Management System can literally run several countries.  I\'m not kidding.  Our new host will be able to keep up with us.\r\n\r\nWith the move we get our galleries back!  Jell-O, Cupcake Fight, and all the rest will be back online, along with the up and coming CHOCOLATE!  Keith is actually flying in from Germany to shoot the thing, so expect great results.  We will also have all our illustrations working, so the articles will make a little more sense to first-time readers.\r\n\r\nWe also have a new team member, IT professional Kevin Bowen.  Kevin is doing all the things that need to get done to help spread the Bitch Kitty gospel, and gives Keith someone to talk to about Arts Technical without having to dumb it down.  There\'s so much to do all the time to manage this site.  Kevin is a much-needed addition and we are thankful for his help.\r\n\r\nWhat else?  Apparel is coming very soon.  I have it on my desk and am just trying to give up sleep entirely to keep up with all the great new stuff on the site.  We have our first band, <a href=\"http://www.heymarseilles.com\">Hey Marseilles,</a> and their incredibly creamy goodness will be available at Bitch Kitty Records with the upgrade.\r\n\r\nThank you all for a wonderful first year!  April 10 is the anniversary of the Bitch Kitty Empire.  Where will you be?\r\n\r\nJohn\r\n\r\nSeattle\r\n\r\nP.S.  Any showing of the Bitch Kitty logo thong gets the Martini of your choice.\r\n\r\nVive la Chat Garce!','189');
