INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('795','body','Markdown','Boxing is one of the purest forms of competition.  I can hit you more than you can hit me.  Simple.  Easy to understand.  If you knock the other guy down, so much the better.  He cant hit you any more.  You win.  At no point in boxing do the combatants ask the judges whose shorts look prettier, or who has the better hair.  \r\n\r\nRacing is the same.  Simple. Easy to understand.  Cross the finish line first.  In 1895, two guys in Chicago bet each other a beer on who could make it to the next bar first.  They slapped together some rules, found a sponsor, and modern racing was born.  Competition has taken on many respectable forms since then, but it all comes down to one simple thing: who is faster.  Thats it.  Endurance racing, the ironman competition of the automotive world, still requires the driver to be faster than the others.  How far the car can go in a given amount of time is dictated by the speed of the car.  \r\n\r\nRacing is not ice dancing or competitive tango.  The tires need to stay hooked to the ground and pointed in the right direction.  Rally drivers who slide the car sideways in preparation for a turn are aiming the car at the turns exit.  They do not ask the stewards if it was cool.  Their performance is not judged on esthetics.  They do not drive for style points.  They do not expect anyone to take them seriously for spastically flailing around corners, ruining tires and scrubbing off speed.  \r\n\r\nDrifting was born of the bad boys of Japan, punk kids who took off their mufflers and made as much noise and trouble as possible.  Its a method of puffing up, its a method of showing off, its a method of being obnoxious, but even I will admit that it takes preparation and skill to keep out of the kitty litter while sliding sideways at seventy miles per hour.  If the style judges were removed and the events results solely based on speedometers and accelerometers, it would be a far more legitimate form of motorsport.\r\n\r\nIf you want to go dancing with your car, paint it pink and slap a tutu on it.  If you want to be judged on style, become anorexic and be a fashion model. Racing is an *objective* sport, with the object being to cross the finish line first.  The *subject* of how pretty you looked doing it is best left to your mom.\r\n\r\n**Links**\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><a href = \"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drifting_(motorsport)\">Drift Racing Wiki</a></li>\r\n  <li><a href = \"http://www.d1gp.com/\">Home to the Official Drift Racing Grand Prix USA</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','247');
