INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('819','body','Markdown','<r:asset name=\"517858425_71f29e7191.jpg\"><r:link rel=\"lightbox\"><r:image size=\"thumbnail\" /></r:link></r:asset>\r\n\r\nKeith\'s household was recently blessed by a little bundle of highly irritating, hairball-barfing joy.  Meet Quigley, quite probably the world\'s cutest kitten.\r\n\r\nLast month, Keith visited John and Kevin in Seattle for a meeting of the Bitch Kitty minds.  There was an immediate surge in the stocks of several local beer companies.  Many pictures were taken, and lots of strange things happened.  [Welcome to our world.](http://bitchkittyracing.com/articles/keiths-visit-days-0-1/)\r\n\r\n\r\n','258');
INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('820','body','Markdown','Reboot9 is Thursday, which means that I am off to Copenhagen tomorrow for more fun in the sun, er 8 degrees. But Reboot is a blast and hopefully some of the faithful characters of the last two years will be back. \r\n\r\nIt seems like I only just got back from Seattle, though it has taken us this long to record what happened. It was the first official BKR meeting, at least face to face and John has all the gory details, with a few of my photos over on the [Main Site](http://bitchkittyracing.com/articles/keiths-visit-days-0-1/). He is only up to the first day. Ah, what fun we had!\r\n\r\nIn any case, please check back for photos from Copenhagen and I promise not to post too many of the [cat](http://flickr.com/photos/sabinebader/sets/72157600277012242/). She is cute though, especially when jumping on my head in the morning.','259');
INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('821','body','Textile','While Keith is toilng away in Denmark at [Reboot 9.0](http://www.reboot.dk/), let us rejoice this Happy Hour in the first few days of Summer.  Let us celebrate with a libation freshly created by Bitch Kitty Racing for the cooling of hard-working, overheated brows.\r\n\r\nh3. Razberi Limeade\r\n\r\nIn a pint glass:\r\nbq. \r\n* Muddle one whole lime with ice \r\n* add one and a half shots of Stoli Razberi\r\n* add agave nectar to taste\r\n* fill the glass with ice, shake, and add soda if necessary\r\n\r\nWhile fruit-flavored vodkas are usually regarded as an evil ploy to introduce children to the wonders of alcohol, as evil as using a cartoon character to sell cigarettes, they can nonetheless have their tasty little uses.\r\n\r\nWhere to today, Marie?','260');
