INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('852','body','Markdown','For some reason, long ago, here in Torino, Italy, someone thought it was a good idea to build a race track on top of a roof. It is a _very_ big roof, sadly no longer in use and not accessible to the general public. But where there are cars, the BKR Team will persevere. Well, sometimes. \r\n\r\nAs a special bonus, the new Fiat 500 was parked inexplicably on the track. \r\n','278');
INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('853','excerpt','Textile','!http://keith.bitchkittyracing.com/assets/393/turin-1009718_thumbnail.jpg! For some reason, long ago, here in Torino, Italy, someone thought it was a good idea to build a race track on top of a roof. It is a _very_ big roof, sadly no longer in use and not accessible to the general public. But where there are cars, the BKR Team will persevere. Well, sometimes. \r\n\r\nAs a special bonus, the new Fiat 500 was parked inexplicably on the track. \r\n\r\n','278');
INSERT INTO `page_parts` (`id`,`name`,`filter_id`,`content`,`page_id`) VALUES ('854','body','Textile','<r:asset name=\"turin-1009718.jpg\"><r:link rel=\"lightbox\"><r:image size=\"thumbnail\" /></r:link></r:asset>\r\n\r\nA few photos from the former Fiat test track at its headquarters in Torino, Italy. A very odd place, indeed, but well worth the effort if your tastes run to abandoned large scale industrial monuments.\r\n\r\nYou can see more photos over at my \"personal--and never updated\":http://keith.bitchkittyracing.com/articles/2007/10/11/lingotto/ section of BKR.\r\n\r\n<r:asset name=\"turin-1009811.jpg\"><r:link rel=\"lightbox\"><r:image size=\"thumbnail\" /></r:link></r:asset>\r\n\r\nIf you are actually interested in this sort of thing, wikipedia has an very interesting \"entry\":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lingotto on the building. Apparently it was in use until 1982 and (this is for your John) appears in the final chase scene of the original \"Italian Job\". I have never actually seen this myself, but John assures me it is one of the best car chases ever. \r\n\r\n','279');
